<h1>So... if it's not just about food, than what is it?</h1>
<p>Food has many ways of fulfilling us, not just our bellies, but our mind, soul, and community.  We are what we consume so do not forget about the food we call knowledge, understanding, nature, and socializing!</p>

<p>Food for My Neighbors is many things, but above all it is a place you can come, discover farm fresh foods, services, information to get you thinking, and a place to show what you've been doing in your community.  If you have homemade items, fresh foods, or even a roadside stand, let us know!  Go right into our <%= link_to "Pantry", pantry_path %> page and post your goods or services!  Maybe you want to post about what your farm offers folks, go right ahead!  Maybe you are just looking to find some organic vegetables, take a look in the <%= link_to "Pantry", pantry_path %>.  You never know what goodies you might find!</p>

<h1>Where do I start?</h1>
<p>I'll start with the reason for this site, I love to teach, inform, learn, and show off!  I love to grow my own foods and I have natural attraction to gardening.  I am, by trade an educator, but I am currently on hiatus raising my two babies who are growing like weeds---or plants, since I wouldn't pull these cute buggers!</p>  

<p>Beyond the teaching aspect, I have grown to love researching about health and how foods and other natural items can hurt or help our bodies.  Since the discovery that I was lactose intolerant among other stomach related issues, I have spent many hours looking up how to heal myself without the need for modern medicine.  Food was both my savior and what created my issues.  Recently I have come across a documentary that I had not watched in a while.  If you do not know where your food comes from or what is in it, you NEED to watch <%= link_to "Food Inc.", education_path %>!  Hands down, it will get you thinking and hopefully changing a few habits.</p>






