	<h1>About My Family and Me</h1>
<p>Well, about me, I am a jack of all trades, but mostly I am looking for a more simple life than I've already lived.  This simpler life came in the form of backyard gardens and the dream of owning property that would benefit our family and our community.  This opportunity is becoming a reality as we are close to closing on a nearly 80 acre wooded lot with wonderful home.  The new land offers an apple orchard, ample garden space, hardwood maples for syrup or lumber.  The land houses three deer blinds on deer migration routes along with opportunity for hunting bear and trout fishing in the nearby Fox River.</p>

<p>This is truly the chance of a lifetime home for my family.  We have all worked hard, sacrificing for this moment.  We are truly blessed to be able to reap what we have sewn and share it with all of you.</p>

<p>What was the hectic life before this, you wonder?  I am an educator at heart and was by trade for five years.  Although I do love to teach and open minds to the wonders of the world, I felt I needed a different platform in which to utilize my talents.  This website and my farm will be my new platform.  Next year my husband and I have some big plans in the works to become an amazing asset to our community.</p>

<p>My family consists of my husband, our two young children, a future puppy, and myself.  Including all the bugs and animals in the world and imaginative world, that makes quite a few of us!</p>
